import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Date', 'CO2'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('CO2 Concentration')
    ax.axhline(y=data['CO2'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean CO2 Concentration')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['CO2'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['CO2'], data['adjusted_CO2'])
    plt.xlabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.ylabel('Adjusted CO2 Concentration')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between CO2 concentration and adjusted CO2 concentration?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['Month'] = data['Date'].dt.month
    chart_data = [data[data['Month'] == i]['CO2'] for i in range(1, 13)]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(chart_data)
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun', 'Jul', 'Aug', 'Sep', 'Oct', 'Nov', 'Dec'])
    plt.title('What is the seasonal variation in CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    mean = data['CO2'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.axhline(mean, color='r', label=f'Mean CO2: {mean:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average CO2 concentration over the entire dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
